library(ggplot2)
data(diamonds)
names(diamonds)
 [1] "carat"   "cut"     "color"   "clarity" "depth"   "table"   "price"   "x"       "y"       "z"      
# 
qplot(diamonds$carat, diamonds$price)

# data
# 
qplot(carat, price, data = diamonds)

# 
qplot(log(carat), log(price), data = diamonds)

# 
qplot(carat, price, data = diamonds,
      alpha = I(1/10),  # 
      colour = clarity, # 
      shape = cut       # 
      )

# 
qplot(carat, price, data = diamonds, facets = ~ cut)

# 
qplot(carat, price, data = diamonds, facets = ~ cut,
      geom = c("point", "smooth")
      )

result <- qplot(carat, price, data = diamonds)
# 
print(result) # 
ggsave(file = "result.png", plot = result) # 
Saving 7.29 x 4.5 in image
#

# ggplot2
library(ggplot2)
# women
data(women)
# 
g <- ggplot(
  women, # 
  aes(
    x = height, # xheight
    y = weight  # yweight
  )
)
# 
g <- g + geom_point(
  na.rm = TRUE, # NA
  shape = 20,   # 
  size = 0.8,   # 
  
  # aes()
  aes(
    # 
    color = height           # 
    # color = factor(height) # 
  )
)
# 
g <- g + geom_smooth(
  method = "lm" # 
)
# 
g <- g + xlab("")      # x
g <- g + ylab("")      # y
g <- g + ggtitle("") # 
plot(g)

# 
windowsFonts("MR"=windowsFont("Meiryo")) # 
g <- g + theme_bw(
  base_size = 24,    # 
  base_family = "MR" # 
  )
plot(g)

# ggplot2
library(ggplot2)
# co2
data(co2)
df <- data.frame(x = 1:length(co2), y = as.matrix(co2))
# 
g <- ggplot(
  df, # 
  aes(
    x = x, # xx
    y = y  # yy
  )
)
# 
g <- g + geom_line(
  linetype = 1,   # 
  size = 0.8,     # 
  color = "blue" # 
)
# 
g <- g + geom_smooth(
  method = "lm",    # 
  color = "orange" # 
)
# 
g <- g + xlab("No.")       # x
g <- g + ylab("ppm")       # y
g <- g + ggtitle("") # 
plot(g)

  diamonds, #

# ggplot2
library(ggplot2)
# randu
data(randu)
# 
library(reshape2)
mdf <- melt(randu)
No id variables; using all as measure variables
# melt()variablevalue
# 
g <- ggplot(
  mdf, # 
  aes(
    fill = variable, # fill
    x = value # xvalue
  )
)
# 
# g <- g + geom_histogram()
# 
g <- g + geom_histogram(
  alpha = 0.5,          # 
  # binwidth = 10,        # 
  position = "identity" # 
)
# 
g <- g + geom_density(alpha = 0)
plot(g)

# ggplot2
library(ggplot2)
# iris
data(iris)
# 
library(reshape2)
mdf <- melt(iris)
Using Species as id variables
# melt()variablevalue
# 
g <- ggplot(
  mdf, # 
  aes(
    x = Species, # xSpecies
    y = value    # yvalue
  )
)
g <- g + facet_wrap( # 
  ~variable, # variable
  ncol = 2,  # 
  scales = "free" ## 
  )
## 
## g <- g + facet_wrap (~variable) + coord_cartesian(xlim = c(0, 1), ylim = c(250,1000))
# 
g <- g + geom_boxplot()
# 
g <- g + geom_jitter()
# 
g <- g + xlab("Species")     # x
g <- g + ylab("value")       # y
g <- g + ggtitle("") # 
plot(g)
